{{distinguish|Mada language (Cameroon)}} {{Infobox language |name=Mada |nativename= |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Plateau State]], [[Kaduna State]] |speakers=100,000, not counting Nunku |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Plateau languages|Plateau]] |fam5=[[Ninzic languages|Ninzic]] |iso3=mda |glotto=mada1282 |glottorefname=Mada (Nigeria) }}
'''Mada''' is a regionally important [[Plateau language]] of [[Nigeria]], with many dialects. It is a highly [[Tone (linguistics)|tonal]] language. A translation of the New Testament into the language was finished in 1999.<ref>https://www.academia.edu/23910111/A_brief_history_of_Mada_literacy_and_the_creation_of_a_Mada_dictionary</ref> Nunku is apparently a dialect of Mada rather than of [[Gbantu language|Gbantu]].
