{{Infobox language |name=Megam |nativename= |states=[[Bangladesh]] |region= |speakers={{sigfig|6870|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Brahmaputran languages|Brahmaputran]] |fam3=[[Bodo–Garo languages|Bodo–Garo]] |fam4=[[Garo languages|Garo]] |iso3=mef |glotto=mega1243 |glottorefname=Megam }}
'''Megam''' is a [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan]] language spoken in [[Kalmakanda Upazila|Kalmakanda subdistrict]], [[Netrokona district]], Dhaka division, [[Bangladesh]]. It is most closely related to [[Garo language|Garo]], but has been strongly influenced by [[Khasian languages]], to the extent that it is only 7–9% lexically similar to with A’beng, the neighboring Garo dialect, but 60% similar to the Khasian language [[Lyngngam language|Lyngngam]].
