'''Vallon Man''' is a term used by the [[British Army]] waging war in [[Afghanistan]] to denote the soldier in a patrol who carries the [[mine detector]]. The term originated from "Vallon Machine", another word used for mine detector (the Vallon mine detector VMR3 was widely used in Afghanistan because of its [[Ground-penetrating radar|unique ground penetrating radar]] (GPR). Using a GPR is the only way to find metal free mines and [[Improvised explosive device|improvised explosive devices (IED)]]. The role of Vallon Man is one of the most dangerous in the fighting in Afghanistan, as Vallon men are often killed in their work.

